cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a generic algorithmic framework for optimization, which is particularly relevant to machine learning and deep neural network training. The empirical studies conducted in the paper focus on various non-convex neural network optimization problems, including multi-layer perceptron, convolution neural networks, and recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
